The paper deals with the problem of detecting face manipulation in videos using deep learning models, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of recurrent convolutional models also suggests a focus on sequential data analysis, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves extensive experimentation to optimize the performance of the models, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the problem of detecting tampered faces in videos also has implications for cybersecurity (cs.CR).
